      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2010-07-15</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2010-09-07T19:52:03Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Preventing Homeowners from Foreclosure Act of 2010 - Directs the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) to implement a competitive grants program for states and local governmental entities to establish mediation programs to assist mortgagors under home mortgages facing foreclosure on such mortgages.</p>   <p>Requires the program to provide the mortgagor with a referral and contact information for a paid or pro bono attorney or a HUD-certified housing counselor.</p>  <p>Requires grant recipients to establish an outreach program to raise homeowner awareness of the existence of the foreclosure mediation program, including a telephone hotline, a World Wide Web site, or both.<br> <br> </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
